1
00:00:01,067 --> 00:00:03,533
<i> Andy Arellano kidnapped you?</i>

2
00:00:03,533 --> 00:00:04,933
<i> Is this Juan's statement?</i>

3
00:00:05,433 --> 00:00:09,633
<i>"I believe that Leon Almazan
got me kidnapped."</i>

4
00:00:09,900 --> 00:00:11,633
<i> What did Sandro's son say?</i>

5
00:00:11,633 --> 00:00:13,400
<i>He said there's a treasure
in Hotel 88.</i>

6
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:16,767
<i>That might be the reason
why Andy wants to take over.</i>

7
00:00:16,767 --> 00:00:19,467
<i> What if there's gold
in the hotel?</i>

8
00:00:19,467 --> 00:00:21,567
<i> We need to know what it is.</i>

9
00:00:22,133 --> 00:00:23,667
<i> If it's even true or not.</i>

10
00:00:24,467 --> 00:00:26,100
<i> This could be one way
</i>of protecting our families

11
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:27,400
<i> against Andy.</i>

12
00:00:33,067 --> 00:00:34,367
Mister Andy?

13
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:36,600
Is this a surprise visit?

14
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:38,067
Luna...

15
00:00:38,067 --> 00:00:41,100
I'd like to personally talk
to you about the partnership.

16
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:43,033
About Hotel 88.

17
00:00:46,133 --> 00:00:53,067
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

18
00:01:45,567 --> 00:01:47,067
Do you believe Justin?

19
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:49,167
[GIO] He's full of nonsense.

20
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:51,767
It's not unusual that he
came up with this treasure hunt.

21
00:01:51,767 --> 00:01:53,800
I couldn't believe it
at first, either.

22
00:01:54,133 --> 00:01:56,800
But if you think about it,
it might be true.

23
00:01:57,633 --> 00:01:58,667
Okay, sure.

24
00:01:58,667 --> 00:02:01,467
If there was a treasure,
Papa would've told us.

25
00:02:01,467 --> 00:02:04,233
What if it's what he was
gonna say on the video

26
00:02:04,233 --> 00:02:05,600
if he didn't get cut off?

27
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:08,167
Gio is right.

28
00:02:08,933 --> 00:02:12,667
Why does only Justin know
about the treasure?

29
00:02:13,033 --> 00:02:14,433
Why didn't we know about it?

30
00:02:14,933 --> 00:02:17,733
Aren't we the sons
of the real owner?

31
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,467
Fine.

32
00:02:26,567 --> 00:02:29,233
Leon said
he was investigating someone.

33
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:31,133
Sandro Soliman.

34
00:02:31,967 --> 00:02:34,100
He used to be Papa's contractor
for the hotel.

35
00:02:35,667 --> 00:02:36,700
And?

36
00:02:37,900 --> 00:02:40,667
[SIGHS]

37
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,667
A few months ago,

38
00:02:43,133 --> 00:02:46,467
he saw Sandro about
to kill Papa and Uncle Fred.

39
00:02:48,133 --> 00:02:51,067
I don't think we're
supposed to talk about that.

40
00:02:52,167 --> 00:02:55,167
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYS]

41
00:02:56,767 --> 00:02:58,533
Leon accidentally killed Sandro.

42
00:02:58,800 --> 00:02:59,800
[KIKO] What?!

43
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,700
Leon killed a guy?

44
00:03:06,667 --> 00:03:08,133
Did he tell you all that?

45
00:03:12,067 --> 00:03:15,167
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

46
00:03:16,933 --> 00:03:21,233
He saw him
about to kill our fathers.

47
00:03:23,167 --> 00:03:24,133
[INHALES]

48
00:03:24,900 --> 00:03:26,800
So, he ran over him.

49
00:03:29,933 --> 00:03:31,967
Leon has been suspecting

50
00:03:31,967 --> 00:03:33,967
that our fathers
didn't kill each other

51
00:03:33,967 --> 00:03:36,267
because he knew
something had happened

52
00:03:36,267 --> 00:03:38,633
that could've been
the reason for everything.

53
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:40,700
That Sandro guy?

54
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:44,867
But...

55
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:47,667
What does he have to do
with the treasure?

56
00:03:48,167 --> 00:03:49,633
[EXHALES] Justin.

57
00:03:50,233 --> 00:03:53,067
He said he's spoken
to Sandro's son.

58
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:55,567
That son told him
about the treasure

59
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:57,233
and his father's involvement
in all this.

60
00:03:57,667 --> 00:03:59,900
And he believed
that murderer's son?

61
00:03:59,900 --> 00:04:01,333
Gio, please.

62
00:04:01,733 --> 00:04:06,833
I know it's hard to believe,
but that's not the worst part.

63
00:04:09,933 --> 00:04:12,867
Sandro is not alone
in his search for the treasure.

64
00:04:16,733 --> 00:04:18,333
Do we know his accomplice?

65
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:22,067
Accomplice, ally,
whatever you wanna call it.

66
00:04:22,067 --> 00:04:23,167
Who is it?

67
00:04:25,333 --> 00:04:26,600
Andy.

68
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,233
[DRAMATIC ZING]

69
00:04:31,367 --> 00:04:34,000
Andy Arellano,
the Almazans' friend.

70
00:04:35,167 --> 00:04:39,167
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYS]

71
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:42,033
[MARINA] Juan is in the station.

72
00:04:43,367 --> 00:04:44,700
Um...

73
00:04:45,067 --> 00:04:47,133
Edward told me

74
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:51,600
that Leon doesn't want
to partner with me.

75
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:54,667
Now, I don't know
where he's coming from,

76
00:04:54,667 --> 00:04:57,267
if he heard something bad
about me,

77
00:04:57,267 --> 00:04:58,767
but let's be honest here.

78
00:04:59,167 --> 00:05:00,667
You guys know me.

79
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:03,267
Your Dad and I have been friends
since you were kids.

80
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:07,833
But, Mister Andy...

81
00:05:08,367 --> 00:05:11,367
I'm sure Leon has his reasons.

82
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,900
And those reasons are?

83
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,067
We haven't talked to him
about it.

84
00:05:19,867 --> 00:05:20,933
Uh...

85
00:05:21,433 --> 00:05:23,300
Can I ask you a question?

86
00:05:24,967 --> 00:05:27,100
[JADE]
Why do you want to help us?

87
00:05:27,300 --> 00:05:31,333
I mean, there are a lot
of businesses out there.

88
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,767
Why Hotel 88?

89
00:05:38,833 --> 00:05:40,767
Because it has something I want.

90
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:46,133
[DARK MUSIC PLAYS]

91
00:05:47,067 --> 00:05:49,100
You know, uh...

92
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:52,867
Hotel 88 is the only prime hotel
on this island

93
00:05:52,867 --> 00:05:54,900
that I still don't own.

94
00:05:55,833 --> 00:05:56,867
When Michael was in charge,

95
00:05:56,867 --> 00:06:00,833
there was absolutely no way
I could get in.

96
00:06:01,900 --> 00:06:03,400
But now that
there's an opportunity,

97
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:06,800
is it bad to try and fulfill
my business goals?

98
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:09,933
Look.

99
00:06:10,133 --> 00:06:13,200
You know, Edward and I
were very happy with Hotel 88.

100
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:14,367
We're very invested.

101
00:06:14,367 --> 00:06:18,067
Because this isn't just
a business between partners.

102
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,000
You know, we're choosing
to do this with people

103
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,900
that we consider our family.

104
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:28,000
[CHUCKLES]

105
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:29,900
Don't worry, Mister Andy.

106
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:32,000
I'll talk to our lawyers.

107
00:06:33,100 --> 00:06:35,033
We'll go on
with this partnership.

108
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,000
Good.

109
00:07:02,100 --> 00:07:05,800
I know Cheska talked about this
on her podcast.

110
00:07:06,067 --> 00:07:10,967
About hidden treasures
guarded by spirits.

111
00:07:12,167 --> 00:07:13,833
But those are just stories.

112
00:07:14,033 --> 00:07:15,200
This one...

113
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,200
What?

114
00:07:17,433 --> 00:07:18,400
Isn't true?

115
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:21,867
Just keep searching.

116
00:07:22,967 --> 00:07:24,200
It can be anything.

117
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:27,333
Diamonds, gold, or something
with a high monetary value.

118
00:07:27,333 --> 00:07:29,400
We've searched
this place before.

119
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:31,233
Raphie almost shook it out.

120
00:07:31,233 --> 00:07:33,333
You're just looking
for documents last time.

121
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,933
But we didn't find
anything expensive.

122
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:39,067
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

123
00:07:40,233 --> 00:07:41,300
It's not here.

124
00:07:43,967 --> 00:07:45,467
You really don't believe it?

125
00:07:46,133 --> 00:07:48,867
If it was a treasure
that Papa knew about,

126
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:50,867
he wouldn't have kept it
in the library.

127
00:07:51,267 --> 00:07:52,900
You said it yourself.

128
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:54,300
In Papa's video, right?

129
00:07:54,533 --> 00:07:57,200
"Don't sell the hotel off,
there's something important."

130
00:08:00,100 --> 00:08:02,000
So, you believe it, too?

131
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:05,300
I'll believe it
if I see it with my own eyes.

132
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:07,300
[EXHALES]

133
00:08:07,300 --> 00:08:08,433
[GIO] How about you, Kiko?

134
00:08:10,233 --> 00:08:11,500
Well...

135
00:08:11,933 --> 00:08:14,933
I believe that Papa
wanted to tell us something.

136
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,467
If it's a treasure...

137
00:08:20,067 --> 00:08:21,067
then, yes.

138
00:08:21,900 --> 00:08:22,933
I believe it.

139
00:08:23,233 --> 00:08:24,900
Then, there should be clues.

140
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:27,433
Clues as to where to find it.

141
00:08:27,933 --> 00:08:29,967
That's what
we should be looking for.

142
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:34,400
Ma'am, thank you so much
for your help.

143
00:08:34,633 --> 00:08:37,100
It's my job to accompany you
even in medical services.

144
00:08:37,867 --> 00:08:39,333
Are you going home?

145
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:42,033
I can't go back to Papa's house.

146
00:08:42,233 --> 00:08:44,133
That's where Andy's men
attacked me.

147
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:45,967
I was about to leave for Manila.

148
00:08:47,100 --> 00:08:48,300
Are you leaving today?

149
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:49,967
I can take you to the pier.

150
00:08:49,967 --> 00:08:51,633
You don't have to, ma'am.
I'm fine.

151
00:08:51,633 --> 00:08:53,100
No, it's okay.

152
00:08:53,100 --> 00:08:54,533
It's not too far off.

153
00:08:55,167 --> 00:08:57,533
- Shall we?
- Okay, ma'am. Thank you.

154
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:03,033
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS]

155
00:09:04,167 --> 00:09:06,900
Ma'am, are we going
somewhere first?

156
00:09:08,133 --> 00:09:09,500
Don't worry, Juan.

157
00:09:10,267 --> 00:09:11,467
This won't take long.

158
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:16,567
Okay, Luna. So...

159
00:09:16,567 --> 00:09:19,133
I'll see you tomorrow
for the final signing, okay?

160
00:09:19,133 --> 00:09:21,400
Yes, Mister Andy. Thank you.

161
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:22,967
- Leon--
- What are you doing here?

162
00:09:22,967 --> 00:09:25,533
What's wrong with you?
Are you okay?

163
00:09:25,933 --> 00:09:28,233
You couldn't buy me off,
so you beat me up?

164
00:09:28,267 --> 00:09:31,067
Leon! What's going on with you?

165
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:34,600
And now, you're trying
to buy my sisters off?

166
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:38,567
Leon, what are you saying?
Let's about this in private.

167
00:09:38,967 --> 00:09:40,533
I know what you're trying to do.

168
00:09:41,367 --> 00:09:42,633
You're an evil man!

169
00:09:42,633 --> 00:09:44,633
Leon, what's going on?!

170
00:09:44,633 --> 00:09:47,267
Why are you so mad at him?

171
00:09:47,267 --> 00:09:49,533
[ANDY] You know what?
Go on, tell them.

172
00:09:49,933 --> 00:09:51,400
Actually, tell us.

173
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:53,967
What's going on?
I'm confused, too.

174
00:09:53,967 --> 00:09:55,200
Have I done something wrong?

175
00:09:56,633 --> 00:09:58,667
- Leon, Leon!
- Leave us alone.

176
00:09:58,667 --> 00:10:00,900
Leave my family alone!

177
00:10:01,667 --> 00:10:04,567
Get out of my house
and never come back!

178
00:10:04,567 --> 00:10:06,133
[JADE] Leon, please.

179
00:10:07,100 --> 00:10:08,200
Luna, go inside!

180
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:10,300
Just go inside!

181
00:10:10,300 --> 00:10:12,533
Leon, Justin,
this is so embarrassing!

182
00:10:12,533 --> 00:10:14,867
Either you go inside,
or I'll kick you out.

183
00:10:14,867 --> 00:10:16,533
[JUSTIN]
He's serious, Luna.

184
00:10:16,533 --> 00:10:17,733
[JADE] Please, Luna.

185
00:10:17,733 --> 00:10:20,933
[LEON BREATHING HEAVILY]

186
00:10:20,933 --> 00:10:21,900
[JUSTIN GRUNTS]

187
00:10:21,900 --> 00:10:23,733
Uncle Andy, I'm so sorry.

188
00:10:25,367 --> 00:10:26,533
[JUSTIN] Calm down, Leon.

189
00:10:26,533 --> 00:10:31,567
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

190
00:10:31,567 --> 00:10:32,567
[LEON GRUNTS ANGRILY]

191
00:10:32,567 --> 00:10:39,567
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

192
00:10:45,567 --> 00:10:46,767
[LEON SIGHS]

193
00:10:50,767 --> 00:10:51,900
[TIRES SCREECH]

194
00:10:52,733 --> 00:10:55,500
Ma'am, this isn't
the transport terminal.

195
00:10:58,033 --> 00:10:59,000
[DOOR OPENS]

196
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:00,067
Whoa! Hey!

197
00:11:00,067 --> 00:11:02,333
Let me go! Let me go!

198
00:11:02,333 --> 00:11:03,467
[THUDS]

199
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:07,833
- [GUN COCKS]
- [JUAN SHOUTING, PANTING]

200
00:11:07,867 --> 00:11:09,533
They've been looking for you.

201
00:11:09,533 --> 00:11:15,600
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

202
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:17,000
How dare you, Leon!

203
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:19,967
Justin, how could you let him
insult Uncle Andy?

204
00:11:19,967 --> 00:11:22,867
He only wants
what's best for us!

205
00:11:22,867 --> 00:11:24,100
You're smart, Luna.

206
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:25,800
But you're not using
your brain!

207
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:28,400
Even if I were the
smartest person in the world,

208
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:30,100
I wouldn't understand
what's going on in your head

209
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:32,333
because you're not
telling me anything!

210
00:11:32,333 --> 00:11:35,000
You're hiding something too,
Justin!

211
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:37,633
There are things
you're not telling us.

212
00:11:37,633 --> 00:11:39,333
Leon, please.

213
00:11:39,333 --> 00:11:40,933
Tell us the truth!

214
00:11:40,933 --> 00:11:43,567
What are you hiding, huh?
What do you know?!

215
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:45,733
Do you really want
to know the truth?!

216
00:11:45,733 --> 00:11:46,900
- Fine!
- [SLAMS TABLE]

217
00:11:47,700 --> 00:11:50,067
Uncle Andy was the one
who had me beat up!

218
00:11:50,067 --> 00:11:51,067
[LUNA SCOFFS]

219
00:11:52,033 --> 00:11:53,700
You already heard that earlier,

220
00:11:53,700 --> 00:11:54,933
but what?

221
00:11:54,933 --> 00:11:58,500
- You had no reaction!
- Because it doesn't make sense!

222
00:11:58,500 --> 00:11:59,800
Why would he do that?

223
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:02,600
Because I'm investigating
Dad and Uncle Michael's deaths.

224
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:04,933
But the case is already closed!

225
00:12:04,933 --> 00:12:05,733
It was Roi!

226
00:12:05,733 --> 00:12:08,467
Roi was the one
who killed them!

227
00:12:08,467 --> 00:12:09,833
That's not true.

228
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:14,567
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

229
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:16,400
What are you saying?

230
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:23,767
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

231
00:12:26,900 --> 00:12:28,500
Because I killed someone.

232
00:12:29,067 --> 00:12:31,667
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

233
00:12:31,667 --> 00:12:33,000
Leon...

234
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:36,667
You killed someone?

235
00:12:36,667 --> 00:12:43,633
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

236
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:47,867
Before Dad and
Uncle Michael died...

237
00:12:49,167 --> 00:12:50,667
I saw them.

238
00:12:53,033 --> 00:12:54,967
Someone wanted them dead.

239
00:12:54,967 --> 00:13:01,900
[MUSIC TURNS UNSETTLING]

240
00:13:03,467 --> 00:13:04,967
So I ran over him.

241
00:13:05,833 --> 00:13:07,433
I killed him.

242
00:13:07,433 --> 00:13:09,900
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

243
00:13:09,900 --> 00:13:11,900
I didn't mean to kill him.

244
00:13:13,133 --> 00:13:15,167
But that guy is a monster.

245
00:13:16,067 --> 00:13:17,800
If I hadn't killed him...

246
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:20,533
If I hadn't done that...

247
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:23,067
Dad and Uncle Michael
would've died.

248
00:13:24,900 --> 00:13:25,933
What?!

249
00:13:26,967 --> 00:13:28,067
Who was it?!

250
00:13:29,967 --> 00:13:31,633
It was Sandro Soliman.

251
00:13:33,467 --> 00:13:34,600
Juan's father?

252
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:41,567
[UNSETTLING MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

253
00:13:42,733 --> 00:13:44,633
Is that why Juan
has been following you?

254
00:13:47,033 --> 00:13:48,633
Maybe!

255
00:13:48,633 --> 00:13:49,933
But Dad said

256
00:13:49,933 --> 00:13:52,033
he and Uncle Michael
handled everything.

257
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:54,533
That I shouldn't tell
anyone what happened.

258
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:57,700
To forget all about it.

259
00:13:59,533 --> 00:14:02,733
And you hid that from us,
Leon?

260
00:14:02,733 --> 00:14:09,633
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

261
00:14:10,700 --> 00:14:13,633
But what does that
have to do with Uncle Andy?

262
00:14:16,733 --> 00:14:21,200
Because Uncle Andy and
Sandro, who wanted Dad dead...

263
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:23,900
...were working together.

264
00:14:23,900 --> 00:14:30,500
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

265
00:14:30,533 --> 00:14:32,200
But how?

266
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:34,767
Why would they do that,
Leon?

267
00:14:35,633 --> 00:14:37,567
Believe it or not...

268
00:14:38,133 --> 00:14:41,867
there's a treasure
hidden in Hotel 88.

269
00:14:41,867 --> 00:14:48,800
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

270
00:14:53,900 --> 00:14:55,200
Damn you, Leon!

271
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:57,100
You ruined all my plans.

272
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:58,700
[CELLPHONE RINGING]

273
00:15:00,167 --> 00:15:02,533
[RINGING CONTINUES]

274
00:15:02,567 --> 00:15:04,833
What? I'm not in the mood.

275
00:15:04,833 --> 00:15:06,233
[MARINA] I can fix that.

276
00:15:06,233 --> 00:15:07,533
[SIGHS]

277
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:09,167
Okay.

278
00:15:11,833 --> 00:15:13,167
We have Juan.

279
00:15:14,100 --> 00:15:15,000
[SCOFFS]

280
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:17,167
[SIGHS] Okay.

281
00:15:18,100 --> 00:15:19,233
Okay, that's good.

282
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:22,667
What are we going
to do with him?

283
00:15:22,667 --> 00:15:29,700
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

284
00:15:29,700 --> 00:15:30,767
[MARINA] Copy, boss.

285
00:15:31,833 --> 00:15:32,833
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

286
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:43,133
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

287
00:15:45,167 --> 00:15:49,267
I find this so-called
treasure hard to believe.

288
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:53,067
Even what you've discovered,
Justin.

289
00:15:55,333 --> 00:15:56,367
I know.

290
00:15:58,333 --> 00:15:59,600
Even Leon and I
don't believe it.

291
00:16:02,267 --> 00:16:06,467
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

292
00:16:06,467 --> 00:16:09,567
I found a burner phone
near where I killed Sandro.

293
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:13,133
I didn't know who owned it

294
00:16:13,133 --> 00:16:15,400
or what I was going
to do with it but,

295
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:16,900
one day,

296
00:16:16,900 --> 00:16:19,467
we were at the hotel
with Uncle Andy...

297
00:16:20,300 --> 00:16:21,433
the phone rang.

298
00:16:23,667 --> 00:16:27,633
It was Uncle Andy.

299
00:16:28,967 --> 00:16:30,900
He thought I was Sandro.

300
00:16:32,267 --> 00:16:34,500
That's how I found out
they were working together.

301
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:39,633
Are you saying that...

302
00:16:39,633 --> 00:16:42,600
Uncle Andy had something
to do with Dad's death?

303
00:16:44,667 --> 00:16:46,233
I'm not sure, Jade.

304
00:16:47,667 --> 00:16:51,000
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

305
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:52,133
I'm sorry.

306
00:16:53,633 --> 00:16:54,900
I'm sorry.

307
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:58,967
I tried to protect
all of you.

308
00:16:58,967 --> 00:17:01,000
So I kept all of this
to myself.

309
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:04,233
I'm sorry.

310
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:09,267
You need to believe us,
Luna.

311
00:17:10,233 --> 00:17:12,567
Whether Uncle Andy
was involved

312
00:17:12,567 --> 00:17:13,600
or not...

313
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:16,233
it's clear he's only using us

314
00:17:16,233 --> 00:17:18,400
to get what he wants
from Hotel 88.

315
00:17:20,100 --> 00:17:23,533
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

316
00:17:23,533 --> 00:17:26,100
Uncle Andy is dangerous.

317
00:17:27,467 --> 00:17:28,733
That's the truth.

318
00:17:28,733 --> 00:17:32,333
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

319
00:17:32,333 --> 00:17:34,200
[JADE] I'm sorry, Leon.

320
00:17:36,100 --> 00:17:38,433
I'm sorry you had to
go through this alone.

321
00:17:40,467 --> 00:17:42,367
Leon, I'm really sorry.

322
00:17:43,733 --> 00:17:45,467
[JADE SNIFFLES, EXHALES]

323
00:17:45,467 --> 00:17:50,533
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

324
00:17:50,567 --> 00:17:51,733
Leon.

325
00:17:57,067 --> 00:17:58,233
Justin.

326
00:18:01,233 --> 00:18:08,200
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

327
00:18:20,033 --> 00:18:21,433
[PAGES FLIPPING]

328
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:27,367
[PAPERS RUSTLING]

329
00:18:30,467 --> 00:18:32,567
Can we just give up?

330
00:18:32,567 --> 00:18:34,333
We're not leaving empty-handed.

331
00:18:34,333 --> 00:18:36,267
We've turned the place
upside down already.

332
00:18:36,267 --> 00:18:39,433
Monette and Raphie
have checked everything too.

333
00:18:39,433 --> 00:18:40,733
Even Papa's library.

334
00:18:40,733 --> 00:18:43,200
There are no clues here.

335
00:18:45,233 --> 00:18:47,133
I'm out of here.

336
00:18:47,133 --> 00:18:48,700
Wait a minute!

337
00:18:48,700 --> 00:18:50,533
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

338
00:18:50,533 --> 00:18:52,333
Is this also a cabinet?

339
00:18:52,333 --> 00:18:55,500
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

340
00:18:55,533 --> 00:18:56,800
[PANEL CLANKS]

341
00:18:57,800 --> 00:18:59,633
[SLIDES OPEN]

342
00:19:01,233 --> 00:19:07,233
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

343
00:19:07,233 --> 00:19:08,400
Check it out.

344
00:19:09,300 --> 00:19:10,333
Give it to me.

345
00:19:13,433 --> 00:19:14,400
[MARTIN] It's empty.

346
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:15,700
[GIO] What? Another book?

347
00:19:15,700 --> 00:19:22,667
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

348
00:19:25,733 --> 00:19:27,300
It's not just a book.

349
00:19:27,300 --> 00:19:34,300
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

350
00:19:48,867 --> 00:19:49,800
[CLINKS]

351
00:19:52,367 --> 00:19:59,367
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

352
00:20:14,467 --> 00:20:21,167
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

353
00:20:21,167 --> 00:20:23,733
[POLICE SIREN WAILING]

354
00:20:23,733 --> 00:20:25,533
[ENGINE REVVING]

355
00:20:28,567 --> 00:20:30,300
[TIRES SCREECH]

356
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:34,900
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

357
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:36,200
Almazan.

358
00:20:36,733 --> 00:20:37,833
Sir Henri.

359
00:20:37,833 --> 00:20:43,800
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

360
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:45,600
You seem to be in a hurry.

361
00:20:47,467 --> 00:20:49,167
What do you want?

362
00:20:49,167 --> 00:20:50,533
And yes,
I am in a hurry.

363
00:20:51,233 --> 00:20:52,600
[MARINA]
We received a report that

364
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:54,667
Juan Soliman was kidnapped.

365
00:20:54,667 --> 00:20:56,567
According to their statement,

366
00:20:56,567 --> 00:20:58,567
you kidnapped him.

367
00:20:58,567 --> 00:21:00,733
[HUFFS] Wait a minute.

368
00:21:00,733 --> 00:21:02,233
That's not true!

369
00:21:02,233 --> 00:21:03,233
I don't even know him.

370
00:21:03,233 --> 00:21:04,400
[MARINA] Syvera.

371
00:21:05,167 --> 00:21:06,167
Check the back!

372
00:21:06,167 --> 00:21:13,133
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

373
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:19,767
Alright, open it up.

374
00:21:19,767 --> 00:21:26,733
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

375
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:34,200
[COVER FLAPS]

376
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:36,667
- [GUN COCKS]
- Don't move!

377
00:21:36,667 --> 00:21:37,867
Put your hands up!

378
00:21:37,867 --> 00:21:42,200
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

379
00:21:42,233 --> 00:21:43,600
[HENRI] Put your hands up!

380
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:47,500
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

381
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:48,500
Put 'em up!

382
00:21:48,500 --> 00:21:55,433
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

383
00:21:57,633 --> 00:21:59,633
[HENRI] You're under arrest
for the kidnapping

384
00:21:59,633 --> 00:22:01,600
and murder of Juan Soliman!

385
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:08,533
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

386
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:16,500
How many times
do I have to tell you?

387
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:17,733
I don't even know him!

388
00:22:17,733 --> 00:22:19,000
[HENRI] But he knew you.

389
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:21,067
He mentioned you
in his sworn statement.

390
00:22:21,633 --> 00:22:24,733
Okay, I may sound arrogant,
but I'm an Almazan!

391
00:22:24,933 --> 00:22:26,867
A lot of people
on this island know me!

392
00:22:26,867 --> 00:22:28,967
Sure. You're right.

393
00:22:29,667 --> 00:22:30,933
But explain this.

394
00:22:31,700 --> 00:22:35,000
How did Juan Soliman's body
end up in your car?

395
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:36,600
- I don't know.
- [MARINA SCOFFS]

396
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:39,767
That's the truth!

397
00:22:39,767 --> 00:22:43,067
Only you and your family
have access to your car keys.

398
00:22:43,067 --> 00:22:44,900
How come you don't know?

399
00:22:45,433 --> 00:22:47,767
How did a body-- a dead body,

400
00:22:47,767 --> 00:22:50,167
end up inside your car?!

401
00:22:50,733 --> 00:22:51,933
I don't know!

402
00:22:52,133 --> 00:22:54,233
I didn't put the body in my car!

403
00:22:54,233 --> 00:22:55,967
You didn't, so someone else did?

404
00:22:56,467 --> 00:22:57,933
So, you had an accomplice?

405
00:22:59,767 --> 00:23:00,767
What?

406
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:03,167
Did you have an accomplice?

407
00:23:03,633 --> 00:23:04,733
I didn't have an accomplice,

408
00:23:04,733 --> 00:23:07,233
because I had nothing to do
with the dead body!

409
00:23:07,233 --> 00:23:11,100
It's impossible for a dead body
to just end up inside your car!

410
00:23:11,100 --> 00:23:12,167
I need my lawyer.

411
00:23:12,167 --> 00:23:13,467
[MARINA] Of course, you do.

412
00:23:13,467 --> 00:23:15,667
I won't say anything else
without my lawyer here.

413
00:23:15,667 --> 00:23:17,567
- Then, you should've--
- De La Paz!

414
00:23:18,767 --> 00:23:20,667
Let's just wait for his lawyer.

415
00:23:20,900 --> 00:23:27,833
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYS]

416
00:23:36,833 --> 00:23:38,833
<i> My brother has no enemies,
so whoever it is...</i>

417
00:23:38,833 --> 00:23:40,067
<i> It's Soliman.</i>

418
00:23:40,067 --> 00:23:42,900
<i>Juan Soliman's dead body
was found in your brother's car.</i>

419
00:23:42,900 --> 00:23:44,067
<i> I need to come clean.</i>

420
00:23:44,067 --> 00:23:46,300
<i>Unless you have evidence,
Leon won't be set free.</i>

421
00:23:46,300 --> 00:23:47,400
<i> Don't drag yourself into this.</i>

422
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:49,800
<i>Don't drag Luna and Jade
into this.</i>

423
00:23:50,333 --> 00:23:53,100
They say, fish is easily caught
<i> by their mouth.</i>

424
00:23:53,100 --> 00:23:55,633
<i>You have to be careful
with what you say.</i>

425
00:23:55,667 --> 00:24:00,133
<i> For me, it's easier if they
</i>didn't know that you're fishing.

426
00:24:00,133 --> 00:24:01,267
<i> What are you doing here?!</i>

427
00:24:01,267 --> 00:24:02,600
<i> I don't understand.</i>

428
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:04,033
<i>- Don't touch me!
- Hey!</i>

429
00:24:04,033 --> 00:24:05,267
<i> What do you want?</i>
